				\usepackage{upgreek}
				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}$x^{k}$\end{document}xk is well defined without any other constraint qualification (CQ).
Under suitable CQ and assumptions including a relaxed positive definite restriction on the Lagrangian Hessian estimate \documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
